The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Kamala Harris and President Joe Biden at the unveiling of the James Webb Space Telescope. The Vice President highlights the significance of the telescope in enhancing our understanding of the universe and praises the international collaboration that made it possible. President Biden expresses his excitement about the telescope and emphasizes the importance of investing in science and technology. The article includes a description of the telescope's capabilities and the first image it captured. NASA Administrator Bill Nelson provides additional details about the image and the discoveries that the telescope will enable. The President and Vice President commend the NASA team and their international partners for their achievements.